-- Vivendi gets two binding offers for SFR
-- By Leila Abboud
-- Wed Mar 05, 2014 03:01PM EST
-- None



PARIS, March 5 (Reuters) - Vivendi <VIV.PA> said on Wednesday that it had received two offers for telecom unit SFR from smaller rival Bouygues Telecom <BOUY.PA> and Altice <ATCE.AS>, the parent of local cable operator Numericable.

Both offers were binding and included financing commitments, it said.